XCOMM Brazilians used to use 'c for ccedilla on us-intl keyboards.
XCOMM It's already taken, but ccedilla is too common in Portuguese to
XCOMM use the sequence <Multi_key> <comma> <c>.
XCOMM <dead_acute> <comma> <c> seems like a reasonable sequence, 
XCOMM given that <dead_acute> starts some 3-key sequences already.
<dead_acute> <comma> <c> : "√ß" ccedilla
<dead_acute> <comma> <C> : "√¬á" Ccedilla
XCOMM since '' is only taken for o and u, use it for cedilla too
<dead_acute> <dead_acute> <c> : "√ß" ccedilla
<dead_acute> <dead_acute> <C> : "√¬á" Ccedilla

